<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" width="100%">
<tr bgcolor="#A0D5FF">
<td valign="top" width="20%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="black" style="font-size: 11px"><b>James Flowers</b>
<br>30 October 2003</font></td><td width="80%"><font><b>So what went wrong with the original Earthdawn?</b>
<br>
<p>Hi all,<p></p>The Compendiums on the roster are intended to be a compilation of the majority of the rules material (read: as much as can be put into them) from the many published supplements and sourcebooks. Unless there's a huge move for it, we're not simply reprinting the old supplements. If you think of the Compendiums as a consolidation exercise, then you will be closer to the mark.<p></p>As for combining other supplements? Absolutely. Denizens 1 and 2 are in the pipeline for that treatment. Dragons and Horrors will likely make their way into the Gamemasters Compendium -- again, a consolidation exercise.<p></p>Why do this? Because on the roster you will also see (and I'm surprised no-one has commented on this) a generic category called Earthdawn Worlds. And this is for non-Barsaive, non-Fourth World Earthdawn supplements.<p></p>We don't have any firm plans in this space yet. If someone has some good ideas then we would be happy to discuss them, but it is there as an option.<p></p>As for use and quality of FASA supplements. I'm not going to debate that here. Opinions are welcomed as to quality and usefulness, but I as I have posted on other forums, I would rather see posters expressing their opinions with some facts and examples if at all possible. That not only adds credibility to one's opinions, but also helps us out by better understanding what the market actually wants.<p></p>If there are products that you would like to see that are not listed, then please LET US KNOW! RedBrick is very happy to entertain new ideas and directions for Earthdawn. If there are products that, historically, you have had quality issues or concerns about, please LET US KNOW! That will help us by ensuring that we don't fall into the same pit with our revised and original products.<p></p>And lastly, thank you for your candid feedback. It is noted and appreciated. We want to see Earthdawn do well in the marketplace. That means producing products that are received and sell well. That can only be done by understanding what our customers want. And your feedback helps us do that...<p></p>Kind regards,<p></p>JAMES FLOWERS<br>Line Developer, RedBrick Limited</p>
</font></td>
</tr>
</table>
